The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 October is 4,635 (536.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 October, there were 409 new confirmed cases (47.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 October, there were 378 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% ( 31 extra cases).
